# Documentation sync

After **substantive** code changes (features, refactors, API or env changes, architecture moves), treat documentation as part of the same deliverable.

1. Follow `@.cursor/skills/sync-docs-with-changes/SKILL.md` (and `@.cursor/skills/sync-docs-with-changes/reference.md` when mapping change types to files).
2. Update only docs that the change **invalidates or extends**—no drive-by rewrites.
3. Before considering the task done for PR-ready work: run the short checklist at the bottom of that SKILL.

Skip when the change has **no** observable, operational, or contributor-facing impact (e.g. trivial rename with zero external docs references).
